{"name":"faux-server","version":"0.2.2","description":"Intercept requests to RESTful endpoints and replace them with requests against the client store.","keywords":["mock","http","isolation","fake","ajax","XDomainRequest","XMLHttpRequest","xhr","REST","CRUD"],"main":"index.js","scripts":{"test":"mocha test.js","debug":"mocha debug test.js"},"license":"MIT","dependencies":{"faux-jax":"^4.2.2","fetch-mock":"^4.0.1","lodash.merge":"^4.0.1","nock":"^5.2.1","qs":"^6.0.2","store":"^1.3.20","uuid":"^2.0.1"},"devDependencies":{"axios":"^0.9.0","chai":"^3.4.1","mocha":"^2.3.4","node-localstorage":"^1.1.2","request":"^2.67.0","sinon":"^1.17.2"},"browser":{"canvas":false,"fs":false,"jsdom":false,"xmldom":false},"gitHead":"0ee1df19d1b05b21d63abb37e60e9b14ec7c708c","readme":"# Faux-Server\n===\n\nIntercept requests to RESTful endpoints and replace them with requests against the client store.\n\n##Usage\n===\n\nRequire and load the faux server.  Once loaded all http(s) requests will be faked out.\n\n```\nvar fauxServer = require('faux-server');\nfauxServer();\n```\n\nOptions:\n---\n```\ndebug: whether or not to log requests to your console. defaults to true.\n```\n\n```\ndelay: delay (in ms) between receiving the request and responding.  Use to fake out network latency.\n```\n\noptions usage:\n---\n```\nvar fauxServer = require('faux-server');\nfauxServer({ debug: false, delay: 100 });\n```\n\n## Disabling faux-server:\n---\n\n```\nvar fauxServer = require('faux-server');\nvar server = fauxServer();\nserver.restore();\n```\n","versions":[{"number":"0.1.0","date":"2016-01-25T16:05:53.121Z"},{"number":"0.2.0","date":"2016-01-27T03:47:07.561Z"},{"number":"0.2.1","date":"2016-01-28T03:05:36.265Z"},{"number":"0.2.2","date":"2016-02-04T05:35:49.173Z"}],"created":"2016-01-25T16:05:53.121Z","modified":"2017-07-22T13:21:28.625Z","lastPublisher":{"name":"bringking","email":"charlie@rinconstrategies.io"},"owners":[{"email":"csteinmeyer@gmail.com","name":"chrisfishwood"},{"email":"jason_hans